    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1492"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/108.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I to-day received following from Villa regarding delivery of Benton’s body:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Very sorry can not deliver Benton’s body at present time. When time comes
                            to do it, I will comply with my obligations, and will give an account of
                            my proceedings to the whole world.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I immediately telegraphed him text your telegram, and reiterated my request.
                    Expect reply in morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
